docs.lead_paragraph: Super Bowl Sunday is the day when the advertising industry is not only tolerated but celebrated. And as in years past, brands paid millions of dollars this year for the opportunity to make consumers laugh, cry and reach for their wallets.

docs.abstract: House lawmakers introduced a bill to clarify Promesa, the bankruptcy-like law governing Puerto Rico’s restructuring, after a New York Times report on one company’s dual role.
docs.snippet: House lawmakers introduced a bill to clarify Promesa, the bankruptcy-like law governing Puerto Rico’s restructuring, after a New York Times report on one company’s dual role.
docs.lead_paragraph: House lawmakers concerned about the possibility of self-dealing and other hidden conflicts of interest in Puerto Rico’s $123 billion bankruptcy introduced a measure on Wednesday intended to strengthen reporting requirements, after one of the case’s most influential consultants was shown to have an undisclosed stake in Puerto Rico’s debt.

headline.main: Transparency of Puerto Rico Bankruptcy Is the Aim of a New Bill
headline.print_headline: House Seeks Clarity on Puerto Rico’s Bankruptcy

docs.abstract: The unusual decision to reopen the case of Alpha Natural Resources to consider possible fraud adds a Virginia judge to the list of officials scrutinizing the powerful consulting company.

docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — A judge in Virginia reopened a more than two-year-old case on Wednesday to consider accusations that the powerful consultancy McKinsey & Company had defrauded his court while advising a bankrupt coal company.

headline.main: Judge Cites ‘Serious’ Accusations Against McKinsey in Reopening Bankruptcy Case
headline.print_headline: Fraud Claim Against McKinsey Prompts Judge to Reopen Case

docs.abstract: China’s WeChat messaging app offers clues as to how Facebook may carry out its shift toward private messaging. But whether Facebook can pull the change off is another question.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — As Mark Zuckerberg begins shifting Facebook to private messaging and away from public sharing and open conversations, the vision he has sketched out for the future of social networking already exists — just not in the United States.

docs.lead_paragraph: Verla Bloomfield has the kind of workplace that seems plucked from a different era. She has a pension, a union, several weeks of vacation and a paycheck that has nearly doubled in 14 years. Her employer? The United States government.
